## Critical Rules
1. NEVER hardcode connection strings вЂ” always use env vars
2. NEVER commit venv/, __pycache__/, node_modules/, .env files
3. NEVER store plaintext passwords вЂ” bcrypt only
4. ALL inter-service communication uses service names, not IPs
5. Every Kafka message must be JSON-serializable with a correlation_id
6. docker-compose up must bring the full stack up from scratch
7. README must document how to run locally and on K8s
